                        "description": "<p>This project adopts the local self-built standard database of Zhongke New Life (in-house database, Shanghai Applied Protein Technology)<strong>[1][2]</strong>. When retained by metabolites in the local database. Inter, molecular mass (molecular mass error within &lt;10 ppm), secondary fragmentation spectrum, collision energy and other information are matched to biological conditions. The metabolites in the sample were structurally identified, and the results were strictly checked and confirmed manually. Accreditation level is above Level 2.</p><p><br></p><p><strong>Refs:</strong></p><p><strong>[1]</strong> Luo D, Deng T, Yuan W, Deng H, Jin M. Plasma metabolomic study in Chinese patients with wet age-related macular degeneration. BMC Ophthalmol. 2017 Sep 6;17(1):165. doi:10.1186/s12886-017-0555-7. PMID:28874192.</p><p><strong>[2]</strong> Gu Z, Li L, Tang S, Liu C, Fu X, Shi Z, Mao H. Metabolomics Reveals that Crossbred Dairy Buffaloes Are More Thermotolerant than Holstein Cows under Chronic Heat Stress. J Agric Food Chem. 2018 Dec 12;66(49):12889-12897. doi:10.1021/acs.jafc.8b02862. Epub 2018 Nov 30. PMID:30472851.</p>",
